<paragraph blockId="3.[151,429,513,540]" box="[151,429,513,540]" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,429,513,540]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Hood" authorityName="Hood" authorityYear="1912" box="[151,429,513,540]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Hoplandrothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,429,513,540]" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,353,513,540]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Hoplandrothrips</emphasis>
Hood
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,585,1007]" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">
This genus includes 117 species worldwide, presumably feeding and breeding on fungi on dead branches (
<bibRefCitation accessDate="2019-05-01" author="ThripsWiki" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" publicationUrl="http://thrips.info/wiki/" refId="ref7542" refString="ThripsWiki (2019) providing information on the World's thrips. Available from: http: // thrips. info / wiki / (accessed 1 May 2019)" title="providing information on the World's thrips" type="url" year="2019">ThripsWiki 2019</bibRefCitation>
). More than 20 are described from North America, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Stannard" box="[899,1079,621,648]" firstAuthor="Stannard" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="213 - 552" refId="ref7511" refString="Stannard, L. J. (1968) The thrips, or Thysanoptera, of Illinois. J Illinois Natural History Survey Bulletin, 29, 213 - 552." type="journal article" year="1968">Stannard (1968)</bibRefCitation>
provided a key to seven species from Illinois. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mound and Marullo" box="[310,622,657,684]" firstAuthor="Mound" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="1 - 488" refId="ref7151" refString="Mound, L. A. &amp; Marullo, R. (1996) The thrips of Central and South America: an introduction. Memoirs on Entomology, International, 6, 1 - 488." type="journal article" year="1996">Mound and Marullo (1996)</bibRefCitation>
provided a key to 18 Neotropical species, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Mound and Tree" box="[1164,1436,657,684]" firstAuthor="Mound" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="476 - 494" refId="ref7290" refString="Mound, L. A. &amp; Tree, D. J. (2013) Fungus-feeding thrips from Australia in the worldwide genus Hoplandrothrips (Thysanoptera, Phlaeothripinae). Zootaxa, 3700, 476 - 494. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3700.3.8" type="journal article" year="2013">Mound and Tree (2013)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 16 species from 
<collectingCountry box="[436,542,693,719]" name="Australia" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Australia</collectingCountry>
. Two species of this genus are recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1048,1097,694,720]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Iran</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bagnall" authorityName="Bagnall" box="[1107,1307,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Hoplandrothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bidens">
<emphasis box="[1107,1213,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">H. bidens</emphasis>
Bagnall
</taxonomicName>
is common and widespread in the Palearctic region on dead branches (
<bibRefCitation author="Priesner" box="[829,992,729,756]" firstAuthor="Priesner" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" refId="ref7428" refString="Priesner, H. (1964) Ordnung Thysanoptera (Fransenflugler, Thripse). Bestimmungsbucher zur Bodenfauna Europas. Berlin (Germany): Akademie-Verlag, 242 pp." type="book" year="1964">Priesner 1964</bibRefCitation>
), and also reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[1284,1436,729,756]" name="New Zealand" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mound &amp; Walker" box="[159,421,765,792]" firstAuthor="Mound" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref7395" refString="Mound, L. A. &amp; Walker, A. K. (1986) Tubulifera (Insecta: Thysanoptera) Fauna of New Zealand, 10, 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="1986">Mound &amp; Walker 1986</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[468,516,766,792]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bagnall" box="[526,632,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Hoplandrothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bidens">
<emphasis box="[526,632,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">H. bidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[647,712,765,791]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,184,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[197,1390,179,1862]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Fungus feeding thrips species of Iran (1) Hindsiothrips sisakhti (female); (2) Idiothrips bellus (female); (3) Hoplandrothrips bidens (female); (4) Liophloeothrips arganicus (female); (5) Hoplothrips (female); (6) Cephalothrips monilicornis (female); (7) Cephalothrips coxalis (female); (8) Allothrips bournieri (female); (9) Stictothrips farsi sp. n. (female); (10) Stictothrips farsi sp. n. (male); (11) Pseudocryptothrips meridionalis (female); (12) Megathrips flavipes (female)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3364946/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) was recorded for the first time by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mortazawiha and Dern" box="[1100,1436,765,792]" firstAuthor="Mortazawiha" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="29 - 31" refId="ref6884" refString="Mortazawiha, A. &amp; Dern, R. (1977) contribution to the Thysanoptera fauna of Iran. Entomol Phytopathol Appl Plant Pests Dis Res Inst, 45, 29 - 31." type="journal article" year="1977">Mortazawiha and Dern (1977)</bibRefCitation>
on the basis of two females and two males collected under the bark of trees infested by scolytids in central 
<collectingCountry box="[1384,1433,802,828]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Iran</collectingCountry>
. Subsequently it was reported from Shiraz, 
<collectingRegion box="[643,801,837,864]" country="Iran" name="Fars" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Fars province</collectingRegion>
, on the basis of five females and five males on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koehne" authorityYear="1915" baseAuthorityName="Koehne" box="[1355,1436,838,863]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1355,1436,838,863]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Prunus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
branches (
<bibRefCitation author="Minaei" box="[265,415,873,899]" firstAuthor="Minaei" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="279 - 290" refId="ref6523" refString="Minaei, K. (2013) The Phlaeothrips - lineage of fungus feeding thrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae) in Iran with a new species of Hindsiothrips. Zootaxa, 3599 (3), 279 - 290. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3599.3.5" type="journal article" year="2013">Minaei 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Although 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bagnall" box="[545,652,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Hoplandrothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bidens">
<emphasis box="[545,652,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">H. bidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is usually collected from branches, in the present study one male was collected from leaf litter. The second species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hood" authorityYear="1912" box="[695,882,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Hoplandrothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[695,882,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Hoplandrothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1058,1106,910,936]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Iran</collectingCountry>
, the European 
<taxonomicName authority="Priesner" authorityName="Priesner" authorityYear="1961" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Hoplandrothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hungaricus">
<emphasis box="[1275,1436,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">H. hungaricus</emphasis>
Priesner
</taxonomicName>
, is recorded only on the basis of one female collected on leaves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkhausen" authorityYear="1803" baseAuthorityName="Borkh." box="[988,1178,945,971]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Malus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="domestica">
<emphasis box="[988,1178,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Malus domestica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Bojnourd region, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,363,981,1007]" country="Iran" name="Khorasan-e Shomali" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Khorasan province</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Alavi &amp; Kamali" box="[378,627,981,1007]" firstAuthor="Alavi" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="183" refId="ref5693" refString="Alavi, J. &amp; Kamali, K. (2002) New records of seven species of Thysanoptera for Iran. Proceedings of the 15 th Iranian Plant Protection Congress, Razi University of Kermanshah, Kermanshah, Iran, 1, 183." type="journal article" year="2002">Alavi &amp; Kamali 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Alavi &amp; Kamali" box="[638,699,981,1007]" firstAuthor="Alavi" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="25 - 40" refId="ref5738" refString="Alavi, J. &amp; Kamali, K. (2003) The fauna of Thysanoptera in Bojnourd region of Khorasan province, Iran. Thrips, 2, 25 - 40." type="journal article" year="2003">2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
